drive to Tangkahan via Binjai and Batang Serangan. Afternoon arrival at Tangkahan check in Mega Inn Lodge. </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 03: TANGKAHAN â€“ ELEPHANT WASHING & RIVER SAFARIÂ Â  (B,L)</b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast walking to the elephants station and then join with the Mahout during washing the elephants, and then feed the elephant. After feeding the elephant enjoying Tubing through the river and stop will be made at fantastic Buluh Waterfall where you may enjoy the waterfall, take natural shower, enjoy sun-bathing and swimming on the river and enjoying picnic lunch on the bank of the river. In afternoon arrival at the village you can get in touch with local people, where you can see the daily activities of the local people and then return to guesthouse by walking, arrival at guest house you can take a rest or visit hot springs and waterfall near the guest house. </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 04: TANGKAHAN â€“ BUKIT LAWANG BY JEEP (Bukit Lawang Cottages / The Heritage Hotel / Rindu Alam Hotel)Â  (B) </b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast leave Tangkahan for Bukit Lawang by Jeep passing plantation and jungle road, on the way stop at plantation and several interesting places such as school, palm oil factory (from its outside only) and for enjoying the panorama and witness the activities of the local people. Upon arrival at Bukit Lawang check-in to hotel. </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 05: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ TRACKINGÂ Â Â Â  (B)</b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast walking to the jungle to start a jungle tracking to explore the nature of Leuser National park with their flora and fauna, there is possibility to see Orang Utan on their own habitat and other kind of animal such as Thomas leaf monkeys, long tail macaque, gibbon, black gibbon and other kind of flora and fauna of tropical rain forest. This tracking will take about 03 hours, after tracking return to hotel. Afternoon free at own leisure to enjoy the nature of Bukit Lawang where you can also walking to the village around the hotel </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 06: BUKIT LAWANG â€“ BRASTAGI (Sinabung Hills / Sibayak Intl Hotel / Grand Mutiara Hotel)Â Â Â Â Â  (B) </b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast drive to Brastagi , on the way stop at Sembahe River, passing Sibolangit, and arrival at Brastagi visiting Lhumbini Park with its duplicate of Shwedagon pagoda, then visit fruit market, and Gundaling Hill. Afternoon check in to hotel.</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">Â </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 07: BRASTAGI â€“ SAMOSIR / LAKE TOBA (Tabo Cottages / Toledo Inn)Â Â Â  (B)</b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast drive to Samosir , on the way visit Batak Karo traditional village at â€œDokanâ€, stop at Sipiso-piso waterfall, visiting â€œRumah Bolonâ€ (Long House) the old Palace of Batak Simalungun Kings and stop at Simarjarunjung to enjoy the fantastic view of Lake Toba. Arrival at Parapat crossing to Samosir Island by ferry boat, arrival at Samosir Island check-in to hotel.</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">Â </span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 08: SAMOSIR â€“ EXCURISON BY CARÂ Â  (B)</b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast excursion on Samosir Island by car, visiting several Batak Toba traditional villages at :</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">-Â Â Â  Ambarita : To see stone chairs and tables the old meeting place of Sialagan Kings.</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">-Â Â Â  Simanindo : To see Batak Toba traditional dances and museum.</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">-Â Â Â  Pangururan : To see the view of Lake Toba and Hot springs water.</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">-Â Â Â  Tomok : To see the old tomb of Sidabutar Kings</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">along on this trip also possible to stop at school to see the activities of young children in the school, visiting the village where the people make traditional hand weaving + stop also at scenic places like the graves! Afternoon return back to hotel</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"><b>DAY 09: SAMOSIR â€“ MEDAN / AIRPORTÂ Â  (B) </b></span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\">After breakfast crossing by public ferry to Paarapat and then drive back to Medan via Pematang Siantar and Tebing Tinggi, on the way stop at several plantation, and it will take about 5 hours driving. Arrival in Medan directly transfer to airport to catch the flight to next destination. TOUR ENDS</span></span><br><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span></span></div><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><b><br></b></span></div><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ansi-language:=\"\" in\"=\"\" lang=\"IN\"></span>\r\n\r\n					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                					                                ', '', '<p align=\"justify\">                                                    <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Take a tour through Medan, seeing Maimoon Palace, the Great Mosque and a Chinese temple- evidence of Medanâ€™s cultural diversity. </span></p><p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Spend a morning with Sumatran elephants, bathing the gentle giants and Tubing at Buluh River.</span></p><p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Trek through Gunung Leuser National Park to spot Sumatran orangutans in their natural habitat, an incredible wildlife experience. </span></p><p align=\"justify\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Get the blood pumping with an active adventure around North Sumatra. Venture into the wilds to meet elephants, monkeys and orangutans and take a spectacular drive through highland landscapes. Continue to Lake Toba, the worldâ€™s largest volcanic lake, to explore ethnic villages with distinctive cultures. </span><br></p>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    '),
(15, '05 DAYS / 04 NIGHTS EXPLORE SIBERUT â€“ MENTAWAI PRIMITIVE TRIBE', '<div align=\"justify\"><b>DAY 01 (Tuesday) : PADANG â€“ SIBERUT â€“ BAT OBAY / BAT ROROGOTÂ Â  (L,D) <br></b>After early breakfast, driver will pick you up at the hotel and then transfer to harbor to catch fast boat to Muara Siberut, fast boat leaving at 07.00AM, this ferry will stop at Sikabaluan and continue to Siberut, arrive in Siberut around 13.00PM and meet with our guide, prepare and report to authority for trekking, continue by local canoe motor in the River, stay in Bat Obay / Bat Rorogot.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 02 (Wednesday) : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BAT OBAI / ROROGOT â€“ BUTUIÂ Â  (B,L,D) <br></b>Wake up for a bath in the river. After having breakfast exploring the daily activities of Nativeâ€™s Mentawai tribe such as : making loincloth, fishing and making tattoo and then continue your trip to Butui by local motorize canoe, it will take about 3-4 hours, arrival at Butui village stay at traditional house of Mentawai called â€œUMAâ€. <br><br><b>DAY 03 (Thursday) : EXPLORING THE NATIVEâ€™S ACTIVITIES IN BUTUIÂ Â Â Â  (B,L,D) <br></b>After breakfast in the morning, prepare to explore the Nativeâ€™s Mentawai activities, you will see how the mentawai making poisoneous arrow for hunting and then go for hunting in the jungleÂ  with Mentawai after hunting you will see how they make Sago (main food of Mentawai people) and search for Sago worm and then you will see how to make traditional medicine. Evening you can enjoy traditional dance of Mentawai and also possible to arrange pig feast (traditional dance and pig feast are optional).<br>Â <br><b>DAY 04 (Friday) : BUTUI â€“ MUNTEI (B,L,D) <br></b>After breakfast, you still have time to enjoy and see the activities of Mentawai people and then leaving to Muntei Village by traditional motorized canoe , on the way stop at Kulukubuk to visit waterfall in the forest, you can swim at waterfall and then return to river to continue your trip to Muntei village, arrival at Muntei village transfer to traditional house of Mentawai or to guesthouse for overnight.<br>Â <br><b>DAY 05 (Saturday) : MUNTEI â€“ MUARA SIBERUT â€“ PADANG (B,L)<br></b>After breakfast free at own leisure or explore the village, at noon transfer to Muara Siberut to catch fast ferry to Padang, arrive at early evening in Padang. Transfer to your hotel.<br>Â </div>					                                ', '', '<div align=\"justify\">                                                    Mentawai tribe living deep in the forests of Siberut Island who were still practising the ancient traditions and rituals of their indigenous culture.<br>Learn about the Mentawai Tribe and join in everydayâ€™s activities! From hunting to fishing, youâ€™llÂ  learn every little secret about the Mentawai people. Explore and enjoy the natural surroundings, jump in the river for a refresh, try local food and stay at a homestay with the locals. It will be an unforgettable adventure in Sumatra.</div>                                                    ');

